# Doc to Alphas Skill

When the user asks to generate alpha factors, stock-selection signals, or OHLCV
factor expressions from a paper, report, market commentary, or other document
text, use the local skill package.

Preferred local project path:

```text
.cursor/skills/doc-to-alphas
```

Workflow:

1. Read `.cursor/skills/doc-to-alphas/SKILL.md`.
2. Read `.cursor/skills/doc-to-alphas/references/alpha_ops.md` for the allowed
   fields and functions.
3. Generate alpha expressions with keys `name`, `expression`, `description`,
   and `rationale`; do not use unsupported fields or functions.
4. Save the generated alpha array as JSON.
5. Validate with
   `python .cursor/skills/doc-to-alphas/scripts/generate_alphas.py --alphas <file>`.
6. Use `--correction-context` for failed expressions and retry up to 5 times.
7. Report pass/fail details, assumptions, limitations, and the non-investment-advice
   boundary.
